                      <td height="63"><TABLE width='100%' cellpadding='4' cellspacing='0'><TR><TD width='10%' ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><B>Rating</B><A HREF="limiteddecks.php?shownlast=0&orderby=rating&slope=ASC&searchstring="><img src='../images/up.gif' border=0 width='13' height='13'></A></font></TD><TD width='15%' ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="limiteddecks.php?shownlast=0&orderby=created&slope=DESC&searchstring="><B>Date</B></A></font></TD><TD width='75%'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="limiteddecks.php?shownlast=0&orderby=title&slope=DESC&searchstring="><B>Title</B></A></font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd10.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>01/21/02</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=20785">Driven: Senate Podracing Space Fury (E1only)</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">An amazingly tech LightSide Senate deck that combines some amazing Congressional bonuses with I Did It for a sure-fire win.  So good, it can lose a podrace facing Watto&#146;s Box and still win the game.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>08/31/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=18697">Dredlox&#146;s Type II HardCore Senators</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This is a type II(Ep 1) dedicated Senate Deck.  High Destiny/Multiple Battle Destiny with retrieval.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>12/17/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=20035">A dIsTrUpTiOn, (InVaSiOn StYlE)</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">this deck uses the new objective from theed palace. basically i will take over naboo and drain and more later....</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/12/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19314">E1: My Lord, Are Those Frequent Flyer Miles?</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">My answer to senators being by far the best E1 deck.  In a word, solid.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>11/21/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19794">We`ll handle this/duel of the defense fighters</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This is my type 2 we`ll handle this deck that drains on naboo and in space.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>09/28/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19139">Techish Type II Senate</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">Mess with your opponent.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>11/14/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19727">duel to the death for lighside</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This is another great deck type. with the restriction of the darkside to one jedi this decktype will be predominate in the current ep1 enviroument till Theed Palace comes out.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>12/2/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19886">EP 1 Senate.</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">Type II senate deck.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>09/28/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19137">Type II LS that wins from Info Broker</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">LS Sucks in the EP1 Format if you ask me, but if you want something that wins without Podracing..which I hate Podracing...then go with this.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/3/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19204">my lord we win the podrace</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">type 11 my lord deck that podraces battles and drains on tatooine</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/2/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19186">MyLoRdIsMaUlLeGaL?</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This type two Senator/Maul lockdown deck. It brings the beats, and has a vicious cycle that is just broken in type two.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/15/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19354">a winning hyperdrive deck  type2</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">this deck has not lost a game in the current ep1 format. i have played against the watto, and senate decks too. i dont know how ref3 will change the ep1 environment, but i think this deck will still be big.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/27/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19518">Lott Dod runs for President</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This deck is not really based around that cone head, but he is one hell of a key element. What wine goes good with cereal?</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>09/27/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19133">Type II Maul and Space deck</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This deck uses space to easily win the drain race, I&#146;ve yet to meet a Light deck in the E1 enviroment that uses more than 2 starships.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>09/28/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19140">kedar the black is dead broke</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">you can&#146;t lose &#146;cause it&#146;s totally gay</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/2/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19189">ONE-ARM&#146;s Type II Senators of DEATH Part2</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">This is the updated version with the inclusion of SAC.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>10/7/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19239">Solid Senators from the land of Oz</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">Aussie Senators Rock</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>08/26/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=18592">Fix That Hyperdrive! (EPI Closed Enviro)</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">EP1 Closed Environment deck that&#146;s 3-0 so far. Uses the Hyperdrive objective and podracing.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>08/26/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=18587">You Bet That&#146;s Legal (EP1 Closed Enviro)</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">EP1 Closed Environment Deck using the power of the Senate and Maul. Just helped me win the EPP Maul.</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right'><IMG SRC="../images/dd9.GIF" BORDER=0></TD><TD ALIGN='CENTER'><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size='1'>09/27/01</font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="darkdetail.php3?deck=19117">Ep1:  Drive-by Munchen (THGG)</A></FONT><BR><font size='1' face="Arial, sans-serif">Racing, SAC, and POWER.  Oh, yeah, and some Jar Jar Munchen action!</font></TD></TR></TABLE><TR><TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN="RIGHT"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Showing 1 - 20 of 186 <A HREF="darkdecks.php3?shownlast=20&orderby=rating&slope=DESC&searchstring=">Next</A></FONT></TD></TR></td>
